"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01UB9GT8FGE7kJtvp1Gi9SQw\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01UB9GT8FGE7kJtvp1Gi9SQw\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-25T06:29:42.142Z\",\"uuid\":\"8d14ab10-5d0a-4b22-9bbb-48023042f035\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"28d0893e-34ff-484c-b8b0-8b6acf195426\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"dc50dae0-c79b-483e-9c1a-8b4a484a8325\",\"version\":\"2.1.53\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/consolidate-e2e-tests\",\"slug\":\"compiled-humming-nygaard\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01UB9GT8FGE7kJtvp1Gi9SQw\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Good. Confirmed: for Failure 3, the entire log ends at `session-end`. No git hooks fire because `core.hooksPath=/dev/null` bypasses them. The shadow branch `entire/1ec27f0-e3b0c4` is created at line 14 and never cleaned up.\\n\\n---\\n\\nHere is my complete analysis of all three failures.\\n\\n## Analysis\\n\\n### Failure 1: TestContentOverlapRevertNewFile\\n\\n**What the test does:**\\n1. Agent creates `docs/red.md` with a paragraph about the color red\\n2. User replaces the entire content of `docs/red.md` with completely different text\\n3. User commits with `git commit -m \\\"Replace red.md content\\\"`\\n4. Test expects: no checkpoint trailer (content-aware overlap detection recognizes this is not agent content), and no shadow branches\\n\\n**What actually happened (from entire.log):**\\n- Session starts, agent creates `docs/red.md`, checkpoint saved on shadow branch `entire/46c243d-e3b0c4`\\n- Session ends (phase: idle -> ended)\\n- `prepare-commit-msg` hook fires. It checks `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent` and correctly determines: \\\"new file has no significant overlap (reverted & replaced)\\\" -- `staged_hash` and `shadow_hash` differ. Result: **no trailer added**.\\n- `post-commit` hook fires. Since there is no `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer on the commit, the `PostCommit()` function hits the early return at line 623-628 and calls `postCommitUpdateBaseCommitOnly()`. \\n- `postCommitUpdateBaseCommitOnly` only updates `BaseCommit` for **active** sessions. The session is in `ended` phase, so it is skipped entirely (line 902).\\n- **The shadow branch `entire/46c243d-e3b0c4` is never deleted** because shadow branch deletion only happens in the main `PostCommit` flow after successful condensation (lines 778-794). The no-trailer early return path has no shadow branch cleanup logic.\\n\\n**Root cause:** This is a **CLI bug**. When `PostCommit` takes the \\\"no trailer\\\" early-return path, it does not clean up shadow branches. For ended sessions with content that was entirely replaced by the user, no condensation occurs (correct), but the shadow branch lingers (incorrect).\\n\\n**Why the shadow branch SHOULD be cleaned up:** The session is ended, the user has committed their own version of the file, and no condensation was triggered. The shadow branch data is now stale/orphaned -- it points to the old base commit and the agent's content that was discarded. There is no future commit that would clean it up because the session is ended and the file content doesn't overlap.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Failure 2: TestModifiedFileAlwaysGetsCheckpoint\\n\\n**What the test does:**\\n1. User creates `src/config.go` and commits it\\n2. Agent modifies `src/config.go` (adds `GetPort()` function)\\n3. User overwrites `src/config.go` with completely different content and commits with `git commit -m \\\"Rewrite config.go\\\"`\\n4. Test expects: checkpoint trailer IS added (modified files always count as overlap), checkpoint is condensed, and no shadow branches\\n\\n**What actually happened (from entire.log):**\\n- Session starts, agent modifies `src/config.go`, checkpoint saved on shadow branch `entire/d31062e-e3b0c4`\\n- Session ends (phase: idle -> ended)\\n- `prepare-commit-msg`: `staged